<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,537,637]" pageId="1" pageNumber="353">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,266,537,564]" pageId="1" pageNumber="353">Diagnosis</emphasis>
: The genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Becker" authorityYear="1907" box="[411,563,538,564]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Empidideicus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="353" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[411,563,538,564]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="353">Empidideicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from other 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Melander" baseAuthorityYear="1902" box="[785,970,538,564]" class="Insecta" family="Mythicomyiidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="353" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Mythicomyiidae</taxonomicName>
genera by the following combination of characters: R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[301,326,592,606]" fontSize="6" pageId="1" pageNumber="353">2+3</subScript>
absent (
<figureCitation box="[422,507,574,601]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1282,1307]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,174,1263]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1437,174,1263]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Empidideicus. jirofti sp. nov.: a. antenna, b. right wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3609591" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3609591/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="353">Fig. 1b</figureCitation>
), first flagellomere subcylindrical, second flagellomere long, antennal stylus not reduced (
<figureCitation box="[255,335,610,636]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1282,1307]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,174,1263]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1437,174,1263]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Empidideicus. jirofti sp. nov.: a. antenna, b. right wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3609591" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3609591/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="353">Fig. 1a</figureCitation>
), and spermathecal reservoir with an apical invagination (
<bibRefCitation author="Greathead, D. J. &amp; Evenhuis, N. L." box="[984,1314,610,636]" pageId="1" pageNumber="353" pagination="487 - 52" refId="ref4084" refString="Greathead, D. J. &amp; Evenhuis, N. L. (1997) Family Bombyliidae. In: Papp, L. &amp; Darvas, B. (Eds.), Contribution to a manual of Palaearctic Diptera. Vol. 2. Science Herald, Budapest, pp. 487 - 52." type="book chapter" year="1997">Greathead &amp; Evenhuis, 1997</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Greathead, D. J. &amp; Evenhuis, N. L." box="[1325,1385,610,636]" pageId="1" pageNumber="353" pagination="105 - 224" refId="ref4142" refString="Greathead, D. J. &amp; Evenhuis, N. L. (2001) Annotated keys to the genera of African Bombylioidea (Diptera: Bombyliidae; Mythicomyiidae), African Invertebrates, 42, 105 - 224." type="journal article" year="2001">2001</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
